{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}
[[File:Inonu Ismet.jpg|thumb|250px|<U+0130>smet <U+0130>n<U+00F6>n<U+00FC>]]
The '''4th government of Turkey''' (3 March 1925 <U+2013> 1 November 1927) was a government in the history of [[Turkey]]. It is also called ''the third [[<U+0130>smet <U+0130>n<U+00F6>n<U+00FC>|<U+0130>n<U+00F6>n<U+00FC>]] government''.

==Background ==
The government was formed after the previous government led by [[Fethi Okyar]] fell following the [[Sheikh Said]] rebellion.<ref name="75.y<U+0131>l">''T<U+00FC>rkiye'nin 75 y<U+0131>l<U+0131>,'' Tempo Yay<U+0131>nlar<U+0131>, <U+0130>stanbul, 1998 </ref> The new prime minister was [[<U+0130>smet <U+0130>n<U+00F6>n<U+00FC>]] of the [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] (CHP), who was also the prime minister of the first two governments of Turkey

