In 1925<U+2013>1927, surnames were not in use in Turkey, which would remain true until the [[Surname Law (Turkey)|Surname Law of 1934]]. The surnames given in the list are the surnames the members of the cabinet assumed later.

==Aftermath==
On 1 November 1927, the president [[Mustafa Kemal Atat<U+00FC>rk]] was elected for the third time, and according to customs, <U+0130>smet <U+0130>n<U+00F6>n<U+00FC> resigned and re-formed his government.<ref name="75.y<U+0131>l"/>

